      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "improve: ship 3D rendered lobster favicon for Control UI",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nThe Control UI uses a flat, hand-drawn 2D lobster as its favicon and logo. This PR upgrades that mascot to a 3D-rendered version of the **same lobster**, giving the browser tab icon, the login screen logo, and the installed PWA icon a more polished, modern look without changing the brand identity.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThe four favicon assets in `ui/public/` are replaced in place, keeping the exact same filenames so no markup, manifest, or TypeScript changes are needed:\n\n- `favicon.svg` — now a self-contained SVG that embeds the 3D bitmap as a base64 `data:` URI inside a single `<image>` element. Because the login page and agent logo already reference `favicon.svg`, they pick up the new art automatically.\n- `favicon-32.png` — 32×32 raster of the 3D lobster.\n- `apple-touch-icon.png` — 180×180 raster.\n- `favicon.ico` — regenerated from the 3D art.\n\nNo external assets are introduced; `favicon.svg` remains a single, dependency-free file. `index.html`, `manifest.webmanifest`, and all referencing TS modules are untouched.\n\n## User Impact\n\nUsers see the upgraded 3D lobster in their browser tab favicon, on the login screen, and as the installed PWA / Apple touch icon. No behavioral changes.\n\n## Evidence\n\nBefore / after render of `favicon.svg` (2D vs 3D), both on a transparent background:\n\n![favicon before and after](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/woohahahaaa/openclaw/pr-assets/pr-assets/favicon-before-after.png)\n\nLocal validation:\n\n- `pnpm build` — passed (favicon assets correctly copied into `dist/control-ui/`).\n- `pnpm check` — passed except for the pre-existing `npm-shrinkwrap.json is stale` guard on `main`, which is unrelated to this change (no dependency or `package.json` edits were made; `npm-shrinkwrap.json` is untouched).\n- Targeted favicon tests passed: `src/ui/public-assets.test.ts`, `src/ui/views/agents-utils.test.ts`.\n\n## AI assistance\n\nThis change is **AI-assisted**. The 3D lobster artwork was generated with an AI image tool, and the asset pipeline (resizing to favicon sizes, embedding the bitmap into a self-contained SVG, ico generation) was carried out by an AI agent. The contributor confirms understanding of the change: it only swaps four static favicon assets in `ui/public/` with no code-path changes.",
